Still, I crossed the room. The first chord was shaky, but the second, steadier. As the melody unfolded, it drew out the ache from my bones. The exhaustion lingered, but as the music filled the small apartment, I felt lighter, almost hopeful. Maybe tomorrow I wouldn’t need to bargain with myself. Maybe tomorrow, the music would come easily.
